“The Game “ my new collection ⚡️ 

 “The Game” seeks to generate a conversation surrounding the beauty and treasure hidden in the simple act of ‘playing’. Whether it is a ball, a glove, a bow, or shoe, it seeks to embrace the spiritual and sacred quality of basic sporting objects transforming them into amulets that remind us of who we are, where we came from, and who we aspire to be. 
 
Through a series of bronze sculptures, installations, photographs, and prints,  I deconstructed the gaming experience and immortalized various essential elements of their respective sports to expose their sacred nature and further highlight the religious encounter of freedom that encircles the gaming experience.
 
Taking part of a game provokes a certain sense of belonging that soon becomes a sanctuary for its players.  It becomes a stage in which they are the main characters of a microcosm that transcends prejudice, social inequality, racial conflicts, and gender differences.  It is a world where the focus lies solely on the playerd and the game and its audience.

Text by @ziibou ✨.

Ignacio Gana is a Miami-based Chilean figurative sculptor. His work has a strong narrative, representative of his creative mind and appreciation of the human form. 

Gana’s works are found in collections and museums such as: the Museum of Modern Latin American Art (MOLAA) in California, Museo Ralli Marbella in Spain, Ralli Museum in Chile, and the Guggenheim in Venice. 
Recently named one of the 18 most influential artists in Miami, Gana was also chosen as the official artist of the Latin Grammy Awards in 2017.

❇️ Discover his work now at Eternity Gallery! ❇️

Longines Ambassador 💎
@longines

Cuando incursioné por primera vez en el mundo del arte,
una escultura de @ignaciogana_sculptures se cruzó en mi camino y me hizo soñar. 
Eso ya hace 10 años atrás. 
Hoy, él conquista el mundo del arte mundial como merece, y yo, escribo desde mi tribuna, para contarle lo mucho que admiro lo que me hizo sentir.

Ignacio Gana es chileno, pero sus sueños no tienen fronteras y su talento tampoco y hoy escribo de él, porque a propósito de sus obras, yo empecé a escribir y soñar con vivir del arte.
